FedRAMP Machine Readable Requirements Schema

Type: object

This schema defines the structure for FedRAMP Machine Readable Requirements documents. It is currently in rapid development and may change frequently.

root info
Type: object

Information about the document including version information, general purpose, and other meta data.

 No Additional Properties

root info name
Type: string

The name of the document or policy

root info short_name
Type: string

3 character abbreviation assigned to this document. Used as part of the key for included objects.

Must match regular expression: ^[A-Z]{3}$

root info current_release
Type: string

The currently official release. May not always be the latest version.

Must match regular expression: ^\d{2}\.\d{2}[A-Z](?:\s?DRAFT)?$

root info types
Type: array of enum (of string)

The types of objects included in the document. See IDENTIFIERS.md for explanations.

Must contain a minimum of 1 items

All items must be unique

No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root info types types items
Type: enum (of string)

Must be one of:

  • "FRR"
  • "FRD"
  • "FRA"
  • "KSI"
  • "FRB"

root info releases
Type: array of object

An array of both past and future releases of this document.

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

root info releases releases items
Type: object
No Additional Properties

root info releases releases items id
Type: string

Unique identifier for the release in the format ##.##A. 'draft' may be appended to denote future releases.

Must match regular expression: ^\d{2}\.\d{2}[A-Z](?:\s?DRAFT)?$

root info releases releases items published_date
Type: string or nullFormat: date

A Valid date string or null

root info releases releases items description
Type: string

Description of the release

root info releases releases items public_comment
Type: boolean

Indicates if the release was made available for public comment.

root info releases releases items effective
Type: object

collection of objects that describe when the release will be effective for specific FedRAMP authorization paths.

 No Additional Properties
